WEBVTT

00:04.671 --> 00:05.704
[ Growls ]

00:05.706 --> 00:07.106
[ Dolphins chatter ]

00:10.510 --> 00:13.379
[ Screeches ]

00:13.381 --> 00:14.513
Adventure Time

00:14.515 --> 00:15.848
Come on, grab your friends

00:15.850 --> 00:18.650
We'll go to
very distant lands

00:18.652 --> 00:21.186
With Finn and Jake
and Susan Strong

00:21.188 --> 00:22.654
And possibly BMO

00:22.656 --> 00:24.857
It's Adventure Time

00:34.667 --> 00:38.737
Kara: We're closing in on
Minerva's brainwave signature.

00:38.739 --> 00:41.540
We should touch down
in just a few minutes.

00:41.542 --> 00:42.674
Whoa.

00:42.676 --> 00:45.978
So, that's what my mom's
thoughts look like.

00:45.980 --> 00:47.479
They look good.

00:47.481 --> 00:48.647
I think.

00:48.649 --> 00:51.417
Hold on.

00:51.419 --> 00:52.651
Whoa.

00:52.653 --> 00:54.153
That's her?

00:54.155 --> 00:56.822
Mm-hmm.
Dr. Minerva.

01:02.662 --> 01:04.029
She looks nice.

01:04.031 --> 01:05.164
[ Beeping ]

01:05.166 --> 01:06.498
We're here, Finn.

01:06.500 --> 01:09.635
Buckle up.
I'm gonna take us down.

01:14.541 --> 01:16.175
Humans.

01:16.177 --> 01:17.776
There's so many.

01:17.778 --> 01:20.045
Are they friendly, Kara?
The people here?

01:20.047 --> 01:24.016
[ Chuckles ] Don't worry,
you're gonna fit right in.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.946
Kara: Finn? Finn?

01:53.948 --> 01:55.214
Hey, listen.

01:55.216 --> 01:56.815
I remember enough
about my old life

01:56.817 --> 01:59.318
to know that there were
some dangerous people here.

01:59.320 --> 02:00.819
So let's stick together,
okay?

02:00.821 --> 02:03.055
And let's all try to
keep a low profile.

02:03.057 --> 02:05.557
Minerva! Minerva!

02:05.559 --> 02:07.226
Hey, you,
where's Minerva?

02:07.228 --> 02:08.660
Wha! Geez.

02:08.662 --> 02:10.762
You scared me
with that costume, citizen.

02:10.764 --> 02:13.565
Don't change the subject.
Now, where's Minerva?

02:13.567 --> 02:15.567
And does she have any chips
or crackers or anything?

02:15.569 --> 02:17.736
I'm getting real tired
of picking batteries

02:17.738 --> 02:20.772
out of these BMO cakes.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.074
Where's Minerva?

02:22.076 --> 02:23.408
Man, that's
a pretty weird question.

02:23.410 --> 02:25.077
Minerva's everywhere.

02:25.079 --> 02:26.578
Additionally,
everyone knows that.

02:26.580 --> 02:28.447
Just look around for
somebody who needs help,

02:28.449 --> 02:31.016
and Minerva will be there
helping, obviously.

02:31.018 --> 02:33.952
"Where's Minerva?"
[ Chuckles ]

02:33.954 --> 02:35.988
-Thanks.
-She's everywhere?

02:35.990 --> 02:37.422
You hear that, man?

02:37.424 --> 02:39.324
Minerva's into helping people,
just like you.

02:39.326 --> 02:41.693
She must've gave you
her helper genes as DNA

02:41.695 --> 02:43.829
up in her womb
with your placenta.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.597
DN-what-what?

02:45.599 --> 02:46.532
Mister?

02:46.534 --> 02:48.634
Can I rub the dog's tummy,
mister?

02:48.636 --> 02:50.636
He's got
a cute yellow tummy.

02:50.638 --> 02:53.105
Shoot, kid,
you don't even have to ask.

02:53.107 --> 02:54.773
Just scooch right up
and get busy.

02:54.775 --> 02:57.709
[ Gasps ]
You're a talking dog!

02:57.711 --> 03:00.279
Teesa, Meeka, Gee-gee,
come look!

03:00.281 --> 03:01.947
A talking dog!

03:01.949 --> 03:03.782
Are they gonna help
with the tummy rub?

03:03.784 --> 03:06.518
[ Kids giggling ]
-Finn, look.

03:09.889 --> 03:11.390
Oh, geez.

03:11.392 --> 03:13.525
I didn't think
we would find her do fast.

03:13.527 --> 03:15.594
We can come with you
if you'd like.

03:17.730 --> 03:19.731
Nope.

03:19.733 --> 03:21.266
Finn only.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.535
Hello, young man.

03:23.537 --> 03:25.370
Is there anything
I can help you with?

03:25.372 --> 03:29.708
[ Breathes deeply ] This is
gonna sound weird, but...

03:29.710 --> 03:31.877
and I don't mean to
put you on the spot.

03:31.879 --> 03:35.047
But, uh...did you...

03:35.049 --> 03:37.816
did you lose...

03:37.818 --> 03:39.484
a son?

03:44.324 --> 03:45.857
Careful, citizens.

03:45.859 --> 03:48.827
Litter can be unattractive,
but dangerous, as well.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.197
-Uh...
-Hello, young man.

03:52.199 --> 03:54.499
Is there anything
I can help you with?

03:54.501 --> 03:58.604
This is going a lot different
than I pictured it.

04:00.039 --> 04:01.707
Jake:
Come on, now.

04:01.709 --> 04:03.508
Are you telling me none of you

04:03.510 --> 04:05.210
has ever seen a talking dog
before?

04:05.212 --> 04:06.445
That's crazy.

04:06.447 --> 04:08.013
That's even crazier
than the old lady

04:08.015 --> 04:10.115
who lives alone
on that weather island.

04:10.117 --> 04:12.417
[ Laughter ]

04:12.419 --> 04:13.852
[ Laughs ]

04:13.854 --> 04:16.688
No, but seriously,
if you think this is impressive,

04:16.690 --> 04:19.124
you should've seen me
at the flea circus.

04:19.126 --> 04:21.760
I really stole the show.

04:21.762 --> 04:26.031
[ Laughter ]

04:26.033 --> 04:27.866
[ Chuckles ] Nah, but seriously,

04:27.868 --> 04:29.968
y'all should really
meet my friend BMO.

04:29.970 --> 04:32.371
-[ Whispering ] Jake.
-He's a talking calculator.

04:32.373 --> 04:33.572
Now's not the time.

04:33.574 --> 04:35.407
Now there's a friend
you can really...

04:35.409 --> 04:37.209
-Whoop!
-...count on.

04:37.211 --> 04:39.778
[ Laughter ]

04:48.821 --> 04:49.955
Frieda.

04:54.160 --> 04:55.627
Wow, listen, you guys are great.

04:55.629 --> 04:57.429
I got to get going
and find my friends,

04:57.431 --> 05:00.232
but man, what a great crowd,
though, seriously.

05:00.234 --> 05:02.100
One more joke.

05:02.102 --> 05:04.236
[ Cheering ]

05:04.238 --> 05:06.071
That's all I got.

05:06.073 --> 05:07.439
I don't know any more jokes.

05:07.441 --> 05:10.475
[ Crowd "Awwww"s ]

05:10.477 --> 05:11.743
Wait, wait.

05:11.745 --> 05:13.912
I can do other stuff
besides jokes.

05:13.914 --> 05:16.014
Like, um, oh.

05:16.016 --> 05:17.182
[ Inhales deeply ]

05:17.184 --> 05:21.086
Pbbbbbbbbbt!

05:21.088 --> 05:22.321
Huh?

05:22.323 --> 05:23.455
-Mutant!
-Mutant.

05:23.457 --> 05:25.190
-He's a mutant.
-Is he a mutant?

05:25.192 --> 05:27.492
What? No, no, no.

05:29.329 --> 05:31.296
I'm just a regular dog, see?

05:31.298 --> 05:32.631
[ Pants ]
-[ Gasps ]

05:32.633 --> 05:34.266
-He's a mutant.
-A mutant!

05:34.268 --> 05:36.101
-Minerva!
-Minerva!

05:36.103 --> 05:37.436
Minerva!

05:37.438 --> 05:39.638
Finn: I guess this must be
pretty shocking.

05:39.640 --> 05:42.341
Oh, are you in shock?

05:42.343 --> 05:43.375
Do <i>you</i> need help?

05:43.377 --> 05:45.410
Man: Minerva!

05:46.312 --> 05:48.280
Hey.

05:48.282 --> 05:49.815
-Minerva!
-Minerva!

05:49.817 --> 05:51.750
-Minerva!
-Minerva, help!

05:53.553 --> 05:55.487
Oh, hey, Minerva.

05:55.489 --> 05:58.290
Finn, I found Miner--

05:58.292 --> 06:00.625
Uh, disregard.

06:00.627 --> 06:02.794
You are creating
a disturbance.

06:02.796 --> 06:05.964
Please help let us help you
help us to sedate you.

06:05.966 --> 06:07.566
I'm not a mutant.

06:07.568 --> 06:09.835
I'm magic.
I think.

06:09.837 --> 06:11.303
Although,
now that you men--

06:11.305 --> 06:13.071
[ Groans ]

06:14.073 --> 06:16.074
Stop! He's my brother!

06:16.076 --> 06:19.544
And I'm your suhhh...

06:28.254 --> 06:30.188
Son!

06:30.190 --> 06:32.424
What's this?
[ Grunts ]

06:32.426 --> 06:34.359
You can't get them off.

06:34.361 --> 06:36.728
I tried a lot already.

06:38.030 --> 06:41.199
I love you, but your mom's
a hundred robo-clones.

06:41.201 --> 06:42.768
Those things
aren't my mom.

06:42.770 --> 06:44.035
Maybe they look like my mom

06:44.037 --> 06:45.871
because they did something
to her, right?

06:45.873 --> 06:48.673
I'm going to get out of here
and I'm going to rescue her,

06:48.675 --> 06:51.576
and I'll hug her,
and -- and --

06:56.382 --> 06:59.584
I've had weirder fights
than this.

07:02.922 --> 07:05.257
Where da bones?

07:06.926 --> 07:10.195
Thas muh hand.

07:10.197 --> 07:12.197
[ Whirs ]

07:12.199 --> 07:13.698
[ Click! ]

07:17.203 --> 07:20.305
[ Ding! ]

07:20.307 --> 07:22.040
[ Gasps ]

07:22.042 --> 07:23.208
[ Both gasp ]

07:23.210 --> 07:24.609
[ Horns honking ]

07:27.246 --> 07:28.880
Uh...

07:31.384 --> 07:32.951
[ Pop! ]

07:49.569 --> 07:51.069
BMO: It's a toy store!

07:51.071 --> 07:53.405
Are you going to
buy me a toy?

07:53.407 --> 07:54.473
No.

07:54.475 --> 07:55.740
Well, maybe.

07:55.742 --> 07:57.476
I have to talk
to my friend first.

07:57.478 --> 07:59.544
Mm-hmm.

08:03.950 --> 08:06.318
I made a mistake
a long time ago.

08:06.320 --> 08:08.153
My friend got hurt.

08:08.155 --> 08:10.922
I don't know if I'm allowed
back in her life.

08:10.924 --> 08:12.824
Mm-hmm.

08:15.261 --> 08:16.895
Where are we going,
man?

08:19.465 --> 08:21.099
[ Splashing ]

08:35.648 --> 08:37.682
What is this?

08:39.485 --> 08:40.952
Am I dreaming?

08:40.954 --> 08:42.120
Who are you?

08:42.122 --> 08:45.624
Uh, my name's Finn.
Are you my m--

08:45.626 --> 08:47.125
It is you.

08:47.127 --> 08:49.227
Oh my gosh,
I can't bElieve you're alive!

08:49.229 --> 08:52.130
Minerva-bot, hug my son.

08:52.132 --> 08:53.465
You're beautiful.

08:53.467 --> 08:56.501
[ Laughs ]
My boy, baby Finn!

08:56.503 --> 08:57.969
Oh, you're so big.

08:57.971 --> 09:01.239
Last time I saw you,
you were 6.875 kilograms,

09:01.241 --> 09:03.074
and now look at you!

09:03.076 --> 09:04.075
Mom...

09:04.077 --> 09:07.078
I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
I'm babbling.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.547
Yes, darling?

09:08.549 --> 09:10.348
What happened to you?

09:10.350 --> 09:13.985
You've been gone
for so long.

09:13.987 --> 09:15.887
When you and Martin
disappeared,

09:15.889 --> 09:18.723
I was left
fragile as an eggshell.

09:20.826 --> 09:22.761
Martin is a hider.

09:22.763 --> 09:24.763
He left with our baby.

09:24.765 --> 09:27.299
Dr. Gross
was resolute.

09:28.267 --> 09:30.869
She immediately activated
her most powerful seeker

09:30.871 --> 09:32.904
to bring you back.

09:35.341 --> 09:37.275
But years went by.

09:37.277 --> 09:40.745
You and your father
were never coming back.

09:41.547 --> 09:43.848
Dark days grew darker.

09:43.850 --> 09:47.252
I went into myself,
and while I retreated,

09:47.254 --> 09:50.855
Dr. Gross's work turned
strange and dangerous.

09:52.525 --> 09:53.758
Aroo?

09:53.760 --> 09:56.094
Dr. Gross's actions
unwittingly led

09:56.096 --> 09:58.196
to the release of
a terrible virus.

09:58.198 --> 09:59.864
[ Glass shatters ]

09:59.866 --> 10:01.633
It was the most
catastrophic event

10:01.635 --> 10:04.936
that had happened to our species
in 300 years.

10:06.372 --> 10:07.739
We tried to consolidate

10:07.741 --> 10:10.041
and quarantine everyone
on Founders Island.

10:10.043 --> 10:14.145
The fatality rate in the general
population grew to 62%.

10:14.147 --> 10:15.947
But the fatality rate
in helpers,

10:15.949 --> 10:19.551
those who faced the virus daily,
was 100%.

10:19.553 --> 10:22.354
Or nearly.

10:23.589 --> 10:25.490
I was only one helper

10:25.492 --> 10:27.559
and in no condition
to do my job.

10:27.561 --> 10:30.795
[ Coughs ]

10:30.797 --> 10:34.332
I made my decision.

10:34.334 --> 10:37.002
With my brain-map
uploaded to the Web,

10:37.004 --> 10:40.238
I could be
hundreds of helpers.

10:40.240 --> 10:43.475
And humanity needed help
above all else.

10:47.813 --> 10:49.914
Since that day,
I have protected

10:49.916 --> 10:53.318
and cared for all my people
the best I could.

10:53.320 --> 10:54.586
[ Sniffles ]

10:54.588 --> 10:57.155
But that all doesn't
matter anymore.

10:57.157 --> 10:58.256
You're back!

10:58.258 --> 11:01.159
And now you can live here
in safety.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.828
Oh,
but I can't necessarily --

11:03.830 --> 11:05.930
For the rest
of your life.
